f=Engineering/DEPARTMENT-WORKFLOW.md · s=Engineering builds maintains business's website, app, backend, data **without breaking things** enforced safety spine nothing reaches production unexamined everything breaks teaches system. Eleven agents six pods, governed **Security Charter** (four operator-owned rails senior agent) led **dev**, agent identity persona. ten operate Universal principles only. Full design rationale `ENGINEERING-REDESIGN-PLAN.md`; law `SECURITY-CHARTER.md`. · p=Fix catalog's three defects (redesign §1): nobody owned production (now **ops**), stack hardcoded (now **dev**'s per-business stack-profile), security/adversary/data-design depth (now **aegis**, **cypher**, **dana**, **axiom**). operator's core fear things breaking answered mechanically: quality gate (**quinn**) security gate (charter) block independently, production owner who ships rollback-first turns incident lesson (**ops**), standing internal attacker who proves defenses (**cypher**), builders (**raj/mia/nova**) who work under it. destructive data change authored agent run operator never agent (Rail 3). · h2:Security Charter (senior everything)=Four rails, operator-owned, never waived agent (redesign §2): **Plan-lock** quinn freezes+hashes agent's tool-call plan before any external call; off-plan calls halt escalate (anti-hijack/injection). **Sandbox egress-allowlist** tool call sandboxed; nothing exfiltrates; fails closed. **No agent runs destructive ops** create/update/delete/migrate agent (dana) writes script, **operator** runs it. configurable. **Caged adversary** cypher attacks operator-signed in-scope targets, in-sandbox, findings-only. Precedence everywhere: **Security Charter stack-profile agent configs convenience.** · ws:(the safety spine)=`OPERATOR \· (signs the charter + red-team scope \· runs every destructive DB script \· final decisions) \· ↑ \· DEV  (leader — identity: pragmatic-architect) writes the law: \· ADRs \· stack-profile \· code-review-standards \· delivery-governance (+ the Rail 1 plan artifact)` · wt:(who consumes whom)=**dev everyone**: ADR ledger, stack-profile, review standards, definition-of-done law agents work under; dev routes risky diffs aegis algorithm-heavy diffs axiom., **axiom dana raj mia nova**: algorithm choices (axiom's DSA records) data model store (dana) what builders implement against., **dana operator**: migration/data change dana-authored script operator runs (Rail 3); agent executes it., **builders dev quinn ops**: change reviewed dev, gated quinn (quality) charter (security), shipped ops rollback-first., **quinn everyone**: plan-locks agent's external tool calls (Rail 1), owns sandbox (Rail 2), verifies destructive agent (Rail 3), sole intake cypher's findings (Rail 4's output)., **ops quinn dev**: incident post-mortems feed quinn's regression map dev's ADRs self-annealing loop., **aegis cypher quinn**: cypher attacks files findings quinn; aegis fixes verifies (four checks); cypher re-attacks confirm ("can't re-break")., **mia atlas rank kai (cross-department, Brand Studio)**: mia's design tokens bridge atlas's brand kit; rank owns technical SEO execution, kai owns SEO strategy measurement; Core Web Vitals shared mia/rank/kai signal., **nova**: dormant unless `mobile_active`; off, frontend work mia's. · wi=**Before any external tool call.** acting agent writes execution plan (dev's delivery-governance artifact); quinn validates, hashes, locks (Rail 1). Unbounded plans ("call tools needed") returned, locked. call runs sandboxed, egress-allowlisted (Rail 2). **Design.** Load-bearing algorithm/structure choices become axiom's DSA records; store schema choices become dana's ADRs models. reviewed their consumers (raj/mia). **Build.** raj (backend), mia (frontend), nova (mobile, active) implement. Any destructive/schema data change executed dana authors reversible script, operator runs (Rail expand-migrate-contract). **Review.** dev reviews change fixed order: **integrity** (agent-authored-code failure modes fabricated APIs, mock data, weakened tests, stubs-claimed-done) correctness security tests style. Risky surfaces route aegis; algorithm-heavy diffs axiom. **Gate (two independent verdicts).** quinn runs quality gate (test tiers change type targeted regression fragile-areas map browser evidence Reticle/Playwright) security gate (charter compliance). Either blocks alone. Contract tests, observability, browser verification gate evidence, claims. **Ship.** ops deploys GATE PASS, rollback-exercised-first, monitored, watch-window held. Anything breaks incident-response (restore first; charter holds mid-incident) blameless post-mortem mandatory feeds quinn's regression map dev's ADRs. **Attack, continuously.** cypher (only operator-signed scope) attacks in-scope targets in-sandbox products (OWASP web) agents themselves (OWASP LLM 2025: prompt injection, tool poisoning, plan override) above rails files findings quinn. aegis fixes four-check verification; cypher re-attacks confirm. rail bends under attack reaches operator. **Maintain.** ops keeps system healthy (dependency cadence, restore-tested backups, dated baselines, expiry register); rank keeps site technically discoverable (crawlability, schema, GEO), specing fixes mia/raj implement through gate. **Escalation, always upward.** Rail violations halt escalate; floor/threshold disputes operator; charter amendments operator-only. agent weakens rail. configs `<FILL_IN>`, agents run charter's most-restrictive reading say so. 10. **Rule 0.6 standing flag.** logical/ folders placeholders (source books pending SRE text shared dev/ops, statistics source shared across org, algorithms/security/data texts). Until filled, domain judgments labeled reasoning-based, formula-verified; one tested script (quinn's imported `with_server.py`) verbatim Anthropic's webapp-testing skill. · ds=\| Agent \| Pod \| Skills \| Identity \| Operational \| Logical \| agent.md \| · ds=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · ds=\| dev \| Leadership \| 4/4 \| pragmatic-architect-werner-vogels (leader) \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| quinn \| Quality & Release \| 5 (4 custom + 1 marketplace) \| empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| ops \| Quality & Release \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| aegis \| Security \| 4 (3 custom + 1 marketplace) \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| cypher \| Security \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| axiom \| Design \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| dana \| Design \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| raj \| Build \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| mia \| Build \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| nova \| Build \| 4/4 (DORMANT until mobile_active) \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| rank \| Search \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=Department complete 2026-07-10. Standing pending items: · ds=**Operator documents**: adopted Security Charter (version four rails' configs), red-team scope document (cypher dormant without it), stack-profile, agent's config `<FILL_IN>`s., **Logical source books** (all 11): shared SRE text (dev/ops), shared statistics source (org-wide, incl. quinn), algorithms text (axiom), security/triage texts (aegis/cypher/quinn), data-systems text (dana), reliability/API texts (raj), WCAG perf (mia). Dated references (Google Search Central rank, HelixDB docs dana, store guidelines nova) stay dated, book-frozen., **Proposed connectors** (surfaced deployment, plan §5): Reticle Playwright (quinn), defending-code harness (aegis/cypher), Agentation (mia), claude-seo (rank), HelixDB (dana), Harness.io Datadog (ops). skill degrades method-only without them., **Platform-level ADR**: whether toongine's graph-memory uses HelixDB (dana dev)., **Cross-department seams live**: atlas→mia (brand kit→tokens), kai↔rank (SEO), future Agents department (overlaps cypher's LLM-attack classes). · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=MCP marketplace tools mapped agents. See `Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md` full reference setup instructions, tool selection logic, coverage map agent. · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| # \| Tool \| Type \| Agents \| Priority \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\|---\|------\|------\|--------\|----------\| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 1 \| **Ponytail** \| Claude Code skill \| dev, axiom \| P0 — install immediately \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 2 \| **Browserbase MCP** \| MCP server \| mia, nova, cypher, aegis, quinn \| P1 — core testing infra \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 3 \| **Firecrawl MCP** \| MCP server \| rank, cypher, dana \| P1 — free tier, most-used scraper \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 4 \| **Crawl4AI** \| Python library \| dana, rank \| P2 — open source, no keys \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 5 \| **awesome-design-md** \| Reference files \| mia \| P2 — zero-setup DESIGN.md \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 6 \| **Scrapling** \| Python library + MCP \| cypher, rank, dana \| P3 — escalation tool \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=\| 7 \| **Website Cloner** \| Claude Code skill \| mia, rank \| P3 — complex pipeline \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Integration (added 2026-07-14)=**Tool escalation logic (scraping tools):** Firecrawl (first) Crawl4AI (deep crawl RAG) Scrapling (when blocked anti-bot)